1
00:00:00,020 --> 00:00:05,080
♪ Inside the state a city is built ♪

2
00:00:05,080 --> 00:00:10,190
♪ Where a benevolent emperor resides ♪

3
00:00:10,190 --> 00:00:15,330
♪ Court officials are brave and able ♪

4
00:00:15,330 --> 00:00:22,750
♪ The empress is fair ♪

5
00:00:25,580 --> 00:00:30,710
♪ Princes died too young to ascend the throne ♪

6
00:00:30,710 --> 00:00:35,570
♪ Princesses are spoiled and fragile ♪

7
00:00:35,840 --> 00:00:40,270
♪ Commoners are also the emperor’s children ♪

8
00:00:40,830 --> 00:00:49,630
♪ All are living peacefully ♪

9
00:00:49,930 --> 00:00:54,280
♪ Wish I could live a day for myself ♪

10
00:00:55,000 --> 00:00:59,380
♪ Follow my heart and ethics without distractions ♪

11
00:01:00,710 --> 00:01:03,400
♪ To be a good husband ♪

12
00:01:03,400 --> 00:01:05,970
♪ To be a caring father ♪

13
00:01:06,460 --> 00:01:10,110
♪ We were close when we first met ♪

14
00:01:10,460 --> 00:01:14,710
♪ I hope I can control my desires ♪

15
00:01:15,540 --> 00:01:20,060
♪ To be a worriless emperor and father ♪

16
00:01:21,120 --> 00:01:23,860
♪ Prudence tops all virtues ♪

17
00:01:23,860 --> 00:01:26,480
♪ People build the state ♪

18
00:01:26,750 --> 00:01:30,020
= Held in the Lonely Castle =
♪ May the world be peaceful ♪

19
00:01:30,020 --> 00:01:33,020
= Episode 51 =

20
00:01:35,260 --> 00:01:35,980
Your Highness.

21
00:01:36,020 --> 00:01:37,980
Princess Fukang comes to see you.

22
00:01:46,700 --> 00:01:47,580
Your Highness.

23
00:01:48,140 --> 00:01:48,980
What happened?

24
00:01:54,220 --> 00:01:55,420
My good friend’s husband died

25
00:01:55,420 --> 00:01:56,780
ten days ago.

26
00:01:58,620 --> 00:01:59,940
She’s still young.

27
00:02:00,740 --> 00:02:02,780
Her children are even younger than you.

28
00:02:05,100 --> 00:02:06,940
She loves her husband a lot?

29
00:02:10,500 --> 00:02:12,180
When I was young,

30
00:02:12,580 --> 00:02:13,820
I really envied them.

31
00:02:15,100 --> 00:02:16,380
They were exactly

32
00:02:17,380 --> 00:02:18,700
a perfect couple.

33
00:02:21,700 --> 00:02:26,380
I didn’t expect him to die so early.

34
00:02:30,380 --> 00:02:31,980
Is this her letter to you?

35
00:02:33,740 --> 00:02:35,020
What a nice handwriting!

36
00:02:36,060 --> 00:02:37,260
Can you recognize

37
00:02:37,900 --> 00:02:39,220
whose handwriting it is?

38
00:02:43,100 --> 00:02:44,140
It looks like

39
00:02:44,780 --> 00:02:46,540
fresh flowering branch.

40
00:02:46,940 --> 00:02:47,980
Very special.

41
00:02:49,180 --> 00:02:49,980
But...

42
00:02:50,500 --> 00:02:51,860
it’s different from famous calligraphy

43
00:02:51,860 --> 00:02:53,260
father has showed me.

44
00:02:54,740 --> 00:02:55,820
I can’t guess.

45
00:03:04,340 --> 00:03:05,180
Huaiji.

46
00:03:06,740 --> 00:03:08,500
You’ve been working for His Majesty for long.

47
00:03:09,380 --> 00:03:11,620
Come and see if you know.

48
00:03:20,940 --> 00:03:22,780
The scenery around Tai Lake was dreary.

49
00:03:23,820 --> 00:03:25,700
Clear water ran around Dongting Mountain.

50
00:03:26,420 --> 00:03:27,940
I didn’t see fishes in the water.

51
00:03:28,620 --> 00:03:31,740
They were trapped in diffuse mist.

52
00:03:32,300 --> 00:03:34,020
When I thought of Fan Li and Zhang Han,

53
00:03:34,460 --> 00:03:36,020
a boat full of perches came quickly,

54
00:03:36,620 --> 00:03:38,380
with waves behind.

55
00:03:38,900 --> 00:03:40,420
At dusk, a storm approached.

56
00:03:41,140 --> 00:03:42,540
I had to return along the island.

57
00:03:43,140 --> 00:03:43,980
I had ambitions.

58
00:03:44,580 --> 00:03:47,380
I was too young to live in seclusion.

59
00:03:48,260 --> 00:03:50,060
Why was I exhausted in the prime of life?

60
00:03:50,740 --> 00:03:52,380
Why did my hair turn white?

61
00:03:53,220 --> 00:03:55,020
I had wanted to fish in the cold water.

62
00:03:55,620 --> 00:03:57,300
But I feared birds would be jealous

63
00:03:58,020 --> 00:03:59,820
and fishes didn’t want to bite the fishhook.

64
00:04:00,460 --> 00:04:02,220
I had to boat through the reed marshes

65
00:04:02,820 --> 00:04:04,540
and stare at the lake in silence.

66
00:04:19,420 --> 00:04:20,100
You?

67
00:04:22,300 --> 00:04:23,180
It’s so late.

68
00:04:23,340 --> 00:04:24,700
Why are you standing there?

69
00:04:32,420 --> 00:04:33,420
What happened?

70
00:04:38,300 --> 00:04:39,300
Answer me.

71
00:04:45,300 --> 00:04:46,500
What’s the problem with you?

72
00:04:47,980 --> 00:04:50,460
Her... Her...

73
00:04:50,620 --> 00:04:51,740
Her daughter died.

74
00:04:53,100 --> 00:04:54,500
She won’t let me go.

75
00:04:55,820 --> 00:04:57,500
Even if she believes it was an accident...

76
00:04:59,420 --> 00:05:00,180
No.

77
00:05:00,420 --> 00:05:01,580
She won’t believe that.

78
00:05:03,140 --> 00:05:04,100
She won’t...

79
00:05:04,100 --> 00:05:05,500
She won’t let my child and me live.

80
00:05:14,500 --> 00:05:16,540
I think Su Zimei wrote this poem

81
00:05:16,540 --> 00:05:18,060
when he was drunk.

82
00:05:22,060 --> 00:05:25,380
He wrote it last month.

83
00:05:28,140 --> 00:05:29,460
Later, he died of illness in Suzhou.

84
00:05:30,980 --> 00:05:32,100
Su Zimei?

85
00:05:32,740 --> 00:05:33,820
He died?

86
00:05:35,500 --> 00:05:37,220
He was only forty.

87
00:05:38,780 --> 00:05:40,380
Growing pressure

88
00:05:41,180 --> 00:05:42,620
made him sick.

89
00:05:43,580 --> 00:05:44,340
But...

90
00:05:44,780 --> 00:05:46,300
He built a Canglang Pavilion in Suzhou,

91
00:05:46,500 --> 00:05:48,060
didn’t he?

92
00:05:48,820 --> 00:05:50,140
Father asked me to recite the poem.

93
00:05:51,020 --> 00:05:52,860
I remember he wrote

94
00:05:53,100 --> 00:05:55,100
he enjoyed his life with animals.

95
00:05:55,700 --> 00:05:56,540
And...

96
00:05:56,820 --> 00:05:57,980
And you said

97
00:05:57,980 --> 00:05:59,580
he and his wife loved each other.

98
00:06:00,140 --> 00:06:02,100
What pressure made him sick?

99
00:06:05,220 --> 00:06:05,980
Huirou.

100
00:06:07,580 --> 00:06:10,660
Do you know

101
00:06:11,100 --> 00:06:12,980
why he named the pavilion Canglang?

102
00:06:14,980 --> 00:06:18,620
Is it from any ancient book?

103
00:06:20,220 --> 00:06:22,060
The clean water of Canglang

104
00:06:22,220 --> 00:06:23,580
can wash my tassel.

105
00:06:24,860 --> 00:06:26,420
The dirty water of Canglang

106
00:06:27,500 --> 00:06:28,700
can wash my feet.

107
00:06:30,300 --> 00:06:31,060
Father.

108
00:06:31,060 --> 00:06:31,780
Your Majesty.

109
00:06:33,720 --> 00:06:34,800
You know it.

110
00:06:36,160 --> 00:06:38,440
I didn’t mean to hurt Yaoyao.

111
00:06:39,000 --> 00:06:39,960
I didn’t.

112
00:06:41,680 --> 00:06:43,240
When she first had the disease,

113
00:06:43,920 --> 00:06:45,000
I...

114
00:06:45,200 --> 00:06:47,120
I didn’t give her the handkerchief.

115
00:06:48,200 --> 00:06:48,920
It was...

116
00:06:52,360 --> 00:06:53,400
It was me.

117
00:06:56,200 --> 00:06:57,320
No. No.

118
00:06:57,320 --> 00:06:58,280
Do you mean

119
00:06:59,400 --> 00:07:01,400
it was me who killed the Fourth Princess?

120
00:07:02,120 --> 00:07:03,600
No. No. Aunt.

121
00:07:04,200 --> 00:07:05,520
I didn’t mean that.

122
00:07:05,840 --> 00:07:06,960
I didn’t.

123
00:07:09,400 --> 00:07:11,760
Yaoyao’s death was an accident.

124
00:07:13,520 --> 00:07:14,960
It was an accident.

125
00:07:15,280 --> 00:07:16,200
Accident?

126
00:07:17,320 --> 00:07:18,440
If you didn’t mean that,

127
00:07:19,280 --> 00:07:20,400
why did you

128
00:07:21,280 --> 00:07:22,760
fumigate the handkerchief

129
00:07:22,760 --> 00:07:23,680
with the paper mulberry pollen?

130
00:07:25,400 --> 00:07:27,320
I never meant to

131
00:07:27,320 --> 00:07:28,960
kill anyone.

132
00:07:29,480 --> 00:07:30,680
When Yaoyao first fell ill,

133
00:07:30,680 --> 00:07:31,960
I warned you!

134
00:07:32,600 --> 00:07:33,520
Why did you still hide so much pollen

135
00:07:33,520 --> 00:07:35,000
in your room?

136
00:07:37,160 --> 00:07:38,560
I was jealous.

137
00:07:41,000 --> 00:07:42,480
I’m as beautiful as her

138
00:07:42,480 --> 00:07:43,480
and I dance as well as her.

139
00:07:46,520 --> 00:07:48,280
At the beginning, you were jealous.

140
00:07:48,680 --> 00:07:49,800
What about later?

141
00:07:51,840 --> 00:07:52,960
Later, you wanted her

142
00:07:52,960 --> 00:07:54,440
to have red rashes and a running nose

143
00:07:55,000 --> 00:07:56,360
and couldn’t serve His Majesty

144
00:07:56,360 --> 00:07:57,200
when he went to her chamber.

145
00:07:57,320 --> 00:07:59,360
Then you could take her place!

146
00:08:05,720 --> 00:08:06,680
When Yaoyao broke into your wardrobe for fun,

147
00:08:07,920 --> 00:08:09,560
she had asthma because of the pollen

148
00:08:10,640 --> 00:08:12,800
and then she died.

149
00:08:12,880 --> 00:08:13,920
That was an accident.

150
00:08:16,120 --> 00:08:18,000
But Madam Zhang was ill in bed.

151
00:08:18,880 --> 00:08:20,480
His Majesty stayed with her every day.

152
00:08:20,600 --> 00:08:22,240
But she couldn’t serve him.

153
00:08:26,480 --> 00:08:28,120
Then your dream came true.

154
00:08:29,200 --> 00:08:31,520
Your dream came true!

155
00:08:33,640 --> 00:08:35,280
Why are you crying?

156
00:08:38,320 --> 00:08:40,560
You have only yourself to be blamed.

157
00:08:40,560 --> 00:08:42,680
Lantiao, how many times have I persuaded you?

158
00:08:49,360 --> 00:08:50,160
Aunt.

159
00:08:53,000 --> 00:08:54,320
What’s done can’t be undone.

160
00:08:56,280 --> 00:08:57,800
As long as Zhang Maoze asks

161
00:08:58,400 --> 00:09:00,200
the maid to insist that

162
00:09:00,680 --> 00:09:01,720
Yaoyao died

163
00:09:01,720 --> 00:09:03,720
because of the pollen in my room,

164
00:09:04,640 --> 00:09:07,120
Madam Zhang won’t let me go,

165
00:09:07,120 --> 00:09:09,200
even if she has to suffer, too.

166
00:09:10,520 --> 00:09:11,440
And maybe...

167
00:09:11,640 --> 00:09:12,440
Maybe...

168
00:09:12,440 --> 00:09:13,320
she’ll vent her anger on you,

169
00:09:13,440 --> 00:09:15,760
because you

170
00:09:15,920 --> 00:09:17,680
gave Yaoyao the handkerchief.

171
00:09:23,920 --> 00:09:24,760
So...

172
00:09:26,320 --> 00:09:27,560
What do you mean?

173
00:09:31,320 --> 00:09:34,160
Zhang Maoze is dealing with Madam Zhang

174
00:09:34,160 --> 00:09:35,200
for Her Highness.

175
00:09:37,040 --> 00:09:37,920
I’m thinking...

176
00:09:38,760 --> 00:09:39,560
Why don’t we...

177
00:09:39,760 --> 00:09:40,840
Why don’t we

178
00:09:40,840 --> 00:09:42,000
seek refuge

179
00:09:42,720 --> 00:09:43,720
with Her Highness?

180
00:09:50,240 --> 00:09:51,520
Her Highness is thirty.

181
00:09:51,960 --> 00:09:53,080
She has no children.

182
00:09:54,280 --> 00:09:56,120
Madam Zhang is her enemy.

183
00:09:57,640 --> 00:09:59,320
But we’re not.

184
00:10:00,040 --> 00:10:01,880
She won’t punish us.

185
00:10:03,680 --> 00:10:05,240
Once she gives an order,

186
00:10:06,680 --> 00:10:08,920
Zhang Maoze will stop the investigation

187
00:10:09,600 --> 00:10:11,080
and pick up the pieces.

188
00:10:13,480 --> 00:10:14,520
Lantiao...

189
00:10:17,000 --> 00:10:18,200
I think she’ll play up to Her Highness

190
00:10:18,200 --> 00:10:19,560
right away.

191
00:10:32,720 --> 00:10:33,600
All right.

192
00:10:36,760 --> 00:10:38,400
Come to my room later

193
00:10:40,080 --> 00:10:41,840
and write down the whole story,

194
00:10:43,720 --> 00:10:44,520
saying that

195
00:10:45,600 --> 00:10:46,760
we never planned to

196
00:10:46,760 --> 00:10:48,040
hurt the princess.

197
00:10:49,880 --> 00:10:51,720
That was an accident.

198
00:10:54,680 --> 00:10:55,600
You and I

199
00:10:57,600 --> 00:10:58,560
shall sign it

200
00:10:59,520 --> 00:11:01,200
before giving it to Her Highness

201
00:11:02,680 --> 00:11:06,320
to show her our loyalty.

202
00:11:18,140 --> 00:11:19,820
Are you promoted

203
00:11:20,540 --> 00:11:22,180
and can control the entire palace,

204
00:11:23,780 --> 00:11:25,580
or are you coming to the wrong place?

205
00:11:27,580 --> 00:11:28,540
Look carefully.

206
00:11:29,700 --> 00:11:30,940
This is the Pavilion of Luan,

207
00:11:32,100 --> 00:11:33,340
instead of Hall of Peace.

208
00:11:35,180 --> 00:11:37,300
Sorry to disturb you, Madam Zhang.

209
00:11:37,660 --> 00:11:39,420
But I hear

210
00:11:39,420 --> 00:11:40,420
you’ve been looking for

211
00:11:40,860 --> 00:11:42,940
the maid who escaped

212
00:11:43,260 --> 00:11:44,460
when the princess died of illness.

213
00:11:44,820 --> 00:11:47,140
Deputy Officer Yang hasn’t found her.

214
00:11:47,700 --> 00:11:49,660
I take care of the unclosed case.

215
00:11:50,860 --> 00:11:51,620
Recently,

216
00:11:52,380 --> 00:11:55,540
I’ve found her.

217
00:12:02,260 --> 00:12:03,100
What did you say?

218
00:12:04,860 --> 00:12:05,620
Father.

219
00:12:06,420 --> 00:12:07,660
Su Shunqin...

220
00:12:08,260 --> 00:12:10,020
He wanted to be an official,

221
00:12:10,380 --> 00:12:11,740
instead of travelling around, didn’t he?

222
00:12:12,900 --> 00:12:14,820
Because he couldn’t be one,

223
00:12:15,460 --> 00:12:16,540
he was so depressed that

224
00:12:17,100 --> 00:12:18,100
he fell sick.

225
00:12:19,740 --> 00:12:20,460
Am I right?

226
00:12:22,940 --> 00:12:24,220
He was in the prime of life

227
00:12:25,300 --> 00:12:26,580
and he was talented.

228
00:12:27,580 --> 00:12:29,100
He had ambitions, of course.

229
00:12:30,260 --> 00:12:32,740
He didn’t want to live a casual life.

230
00:12:34,740 --> 00:12:36,500
Father, since you like his talent,

231
00:12:37,140 --> 00:12:38,700
why did you still banish him

232
00:12:38,780 --> 00:12:40,340
instead of letting him realize his ambition?

233
00:12:44,940 --> 00:12:46,260
Because he made a mistake

234
00:12:47,260 --> 00:12:48,420
and he had to take responsibility.

235
00:12:49,180 --> 00:12:51,100
But Her Highness just said

236
00:12:51,340 --> 00:12:52,460
he named his pavilion

237
00:12:52,580 --> 00:12:54,100
Canglang.

238
00:12:55,020 --> 00:12:56,660
You just explained

239
00:12:56,660 --> 00:12:57,900
what that meant.

240
00:12:58,540 --> 00:12:59,620
It means

241
00:12:59,940 --> 00:13:01,540
he thought he was aggrieved.

242
00:13:06,380 --> 00:13:08,460
He’s a pure and honest man.

243
00:13:09,180 --> 00:13:10,740
People admire him.

244
00:13:11,860 --> 00:13:12,980
Friends like him.

245
00:13:15,460 --> 00:13:16,500
But as an official,

246
00:13:17,020 --> 00:13:18,580
he wasn’t flexible enough.

247
00:13:18,940 --> 00:13:19,900
And he was too proud.

248
00:13:20,100 --> 00:13:21,140
His colleagues didn’t like him.

249
00:13:22,140 --> 00:13:24,380
Also, he wasn’t cautious and broke the rule,

250
00:13:24,780 --> 00:13:25,860
he gave a bad example.

251
00:13:27,860 --> 00:13:30,100
He wasn’t aggrieved to be fired.

252
00:13:31,820 --> 00:13:33,420
But when many people took the chance

253
00:13:33,660 --> 00:13:34,900
to discredit him,

254
00:13:35,820 --> 00:13:38,460
it was wrong to him.

255
00:13:40,900 --> 00:13:41,660
I don’t understand.

256
00:13:45,740 --> 00:13:47,540
You don’t need to understand.

257
00:13:48,380 --> 00:13:50,060
But I know

258
00:13:50,380 --> 00:13:51,220
his death

259
00:13:51,220 --> 00:13:52,300
makes you sad.

260
00:13:54,900 --> 00:13:55,620
Yes.

261
00:13:58,580 --> 00:13:59,580
Since then,

262
00:14:01,060 --> 00:14:02,380
such a talent like Su Zimei

263
00:14:03,660 --> 00:14:04,670
who always drinks while reading

264
00:14:04,670 --> 00:14:06,070
no longer exists.

265
00:14:07,780 --> 00:14:09,820
No more new articles from him.

266
00:14:12,000 --> 00:14:14,100
It’s the loss of our nation,

267
00:14:15,540 --> 00:14:16,860
and the regret of later generations.

268
00:14:19,740 --> 00:14:22,100
He isn’t a bad guy.

269
00:14:22,980 --> 00:14:24,300
And he’s talented.

270
00:14:25,060 --> 00:14:26,260
Father, why didn’t you make an exception

271
00:14:26,340 --> 00:14:27,420
and show some mercy?

272
00:14:27,860 --> 00:14:29,220
You wanted to do that, I’m sure.

273
00:14:34,780 --> 00:14:37,140
No one can

274
00:14:37,140 --> 00:14:38,580
do anything

275
00:14:38,580 --> 00:14:39,420
just because he wants to.

276
00:14:40,740 --> 00:14:42,940
Even you, father?

277
00:14:43,540 --> 00:14:44,460
You’re the Emperor.

278
00:14:44,740 --> 00:14:46,380
You control everyone else in the world.

279
00:14:49,780 --> 00:14:52,380
Your father controls everyone else in the world,

280
00:14:53,740 --> 00:14:55,740
but he’s controlled by them, too.

281
00:14:57,140 --> 00:14:58,220
He can’t do things

282
00:14:59,060 --> 00:15:00,380
only because he wants to.

283
00:15:06,820 --> 00:15:07,620
You mean…

284
00:15:09,500 --> 00:15:10,460
Yaoyao didn’t

285
00:15:11,300 --> 00:15:13,020
die of asthma

286
00:15:13,140 --> 00:15:14,100
because she had fun outdoors

287
00:15:14,340 --> 00:15:16,060
when it was too cold,

288
00:15:17,700 --> 00:15:19,580
but because she sucked the pollen accidentally

289
00:15:20,660 --> 00:15:22,420
in a maid’s wardrobe?

290
00:15:24,620 --> 00:15:25,540
That was

291
00:15:25,740 --> 00:15:27,380
what the escaped maid said.

292
00:15:29,060 --> 00:15:30,660
She also saw

293
00:15:31,380 --> 00:15:33,940
a witchcraft doll

294
00:15:34,820 --> 00:15:35,620
in the wardrobe

295
00:15:37,780 --> 00:15:39,460
with your name

296
00:15:39,700 --> 00:15:40,980
and your birth date on it.

297
00:15:42,980 --> 00:15:43,940
Maid?

298
00:15:44,780 --> 00:15:45,780
Which maid?

299
00:15:47,060 --> 00:15:48,660
I’m going to skin her!

300
00:15:48,860 --> 00:15:49,900
Skin her!

301
00:15:49,900 --> 00:15:50,660
Madam.

302
00:15:52,180 --> 00:15:52,900
Madam.

303
00:15:54,860 --> 00:15:57,260
He’s a mean guy.

304
00:15:57,420 --> 00:15:58,300
Don’t fall into

305
00:15:58,300 --> 00:15:59,260
his trap!

306
00:16:00,660 --> 00:16:01,980
Let His Majesty judge

307
00:16:01,980 --> 00:16:02,860
after we report it to him

308
00:16:03,300 --> 00:16:04,980
tomorrow.

309
00:16:08,940 --> 00:16:11,740
I removed Su Shunqin from office

310
00:16:11,740 --> 00:16:12,860
and said I wouldn’t use him again.

311
00:16:14,260 --> 00:16:16,860
But I meant to put down the criticism

312
00:16:17,580 --> 00:16:19,660
and taught him a lesson.

313
00:16:22,540 --> 00:16:23,300
This year,

314
00:16:24,580 --> 00:16:26,540
a new term was added to

315
00:16:26,540 --> 00:16:27,300
the imperial decree.

316
00:16:28,540 --> 00:16:30,820
Those who use little public fund

317
00:16:31,740 --> 00:16:33,300
can be put on probation by the Ministry of Justice.

318
00:16:37,940 --> 00:16:39,060
Censors objected,

319
00:16:40,420 --> 00:16:43,300
saying it was shielding Su Shunqin.

320
00:16:45,300 --> 00:16:46,300
Two months ago,

321
00:16:46,940 --> 00:16:50,260
I reinstated Shunqin

322
00:16:51,540 --> 00:16:52,900
as the adjutant of Huzhou.

323
00:16:54,660 --> 00:16:57,300
I had meant to make him work in other cities

324
00:16:58,020 --> 00:16:59,660
before being transferred back to the Capital

325
00:17:00,580 --> 00:17:02,220
in case of too much objection from censors.

326
00:17:04,020 --> 00:17:04,780
Unexpectedly,

327
00:17:07,340 --> 00:17:08,500
he died before he came back.

328
00:17:13,540 --> 00:17:15,220
I had also expected him and his wife

329
00:17:15,780 --> 00:17:17,060
to live in seclusion

330
00:17:18,540 --> 00:17:20,020
where they could live with nature,

331
00:17:21,140 --> 00:17:22,300
sing as they wish

332
00:17:23,180 --> 00:17:24,220
and stay away from the noise.

333
00:17:26,180 --> 00:17:27,060
But...

334
00:17:27,580 --> 00:17:29,420
Zimei still had ambitions.

335
00:17:29,780 --> 00:17:32,500
He was too young to live in seclusion.

336
00:17:34,340 --> 00:17:35,580
Such a talent like him

337
00:17:37,020 --> 00:17:39,420
can’t be unworldly

338
00:17:40,140 --> 00:17:41,140
or let go of the common customs.

339
00:17:48,660 --> 00:17:50,060
Who could be unworldly?

340
00:17:52,140 --> 00:17:53,100
People want fame,

341
00:17:53,980 --> 00:17:55,020
ambition

342
00:17:56,100 --> 00:17:59,460
or responsibility.

343
00:18:01,980 --> 00:18:03,300
Su Shunqin can’t be unworldly.

344
00:18:04,180 --> 00:18:05,300
Xia Song can’t.

345
00:18:06,060 --> 00:18:09,180
Nor can I.

346
00:18:12,500 --> 00:18:13,980
Your Majesty,
you control everyone else in the world.

347
00:18:14,820 --> 00:18:16,380
They don’t have a choice.

348
00:18:18,420 --> 00:18:20,540
But when you’re controlled by them,

349
00:18:22,020 --> 00:18:23,660
it’s your own choice.

350
00:18:28,740 --> 00:18:30,660
But I’m always unconvinced.

351
00:18:31,100 --> 00:18:33,020
Yet it’s still your own choice.

352
00:18:37,140 --> 00:18:39,420
To make everyone else in the world

353
00:18:39,700 --> 00:18:41,260
be controlled willingly,

354
00:18:44,420 --> 00:18:46,380
you choose to feel unconvinced.

355
00:19:12,860 --> 00:19:14,620
Ask Qiuhe to bring your wine to us.

356
00:19:18,140 --> 00:19:18,900
Your Majesty.

357
00:19:19,980 --> 00:19:21,220
You don’t look well.

358
00:19:22,820 --> 00:19:24,420
I’ll ask Qiuhe to massage you.

359
00:19:25,260 --> 00:19:27,140
I don’t want any advice from the Empress now.

360
00:19:28,980 --> 00:19:30,420
I just want to drink with my wife.

361
00:20:29,260 --> 00:20:30,180
Huaiji.

362
00:20:31,180 --> 00:20:34,220
Do you think all men in the world

363
00:20:34,660 --> 00:20:36,020
want to be an official?

364
00:20:38,500 --> 00:20:41,380
In our nation, whoever marries a princess

365
00:20:41,940 --> 00:20:43,700
can’t work as an important official

366
00:20:44,100 --> 00:20:45,540
or be in charge of politics.

367
00:20:46,060 --> 00:20:46,780
He can only be

368
00:20:46,780 --> 00:20:48,260
an idle Prince Consort.

369
00:20:49,300 --> 00:20:50,260
Is that true?

370
00:20:52,260 --> 00:20:55,140
This is our rule.

371
00:20:56,060 --> 00:20:57,060
But people can be talented

372
00:20:57,060 --> 00:20:58,260
in many other ways, too.

373
00:20:59,260 --> 00:21:01,420
For example, Prince Consort is good at painting.

374
00:21:05,540 --> 00:21:06,420
So...

375
00:21:07,260 --> 00:21:09,340
maybe even though Ping likes me,

376
00:21:10,500 --> 00:21:11,940
he still wants to be an official.

377
00:21:13,180 --> 00:21:15,140
That’s why father didn’t pick him

378
00:21:15,140 --> 00:21:16,340
as my husband.

379
00:21:18,180 --> 00:21:20,460
Father loves me.

380
00:21:21,020 --> 00:21:21,900
Or why didn’t he choose

381
00:21:21,900 --> 00:21:23,180
the best man in the world for me?

382
00:21:25,580 --> 00:21:26,940
I don’t know what Mr. Cao thinks.

383
00:21:27,300 --> 00:21:29,180
Nor do I dare to guess what His Majesty thinks.

384
00:21:31,780 --> 00:21:32,500
Huaiji.

385
00:21:33,540 --> 00:21:37,060
I’ve been thinking about it hard.

386
00:21:37,970 --> 00:21:39,100
I wondered

387
00:21:39,100 --> 00:21:40,580
why father doesn’t marry me to Ping.

388
00:21:41,540 --> 00:21:42,740
Either thinking

389
00:21:43,460 --> 00:21:44,980
it’s because father doesn’t love me that much

390
00:21:45,900 --> 00:21:46,820
or thinking it’s because

391
00:21:47,220 --> 00:21:48,820
Ping doesn’t like me that much

392
00:21:50,780 --> 00:21:51,900
made me very sad.

393
00:21:53,420 --> 00:21:55,580
I’ve never been so sad before.

394
00:21:59,740 --> 00:22:01,220
His Majesty loves you the most.

395
00:22:03,060 --> 00:22:03,860
Today,

396
00:22:04,300 --> 00:22:06,620
father and Her Highness talked about Su Shunqin.

397
00:22:07,340 --> 00:22:08,940
He’s handsome and talented,

398
00:22:09,180 --> 00:22:10,660
with a wife in love.

399
00:22:11,780 --> 00:22:12,580
Instead of being an official,

400
00:22:13,260 --> 00:22:15,260
he built a pavilion in the nature,

401
00:22:15,460 --> 00:22:17,020
wrote poems and painted.

402
00:22:17,580 --> 00:22:18,540
That was a much better life

403
00:22:18,540 --> 00:22:19,620
than complaining about father

404
00:22:19,740 --> 00:22:21,100
and quarreling with

405
00:22:21,100 --> 00:22:21,980
other old officials.

406
00:22:23,100 --> 00:22:25,700
But because he failed to be an official,

407
00:22:26,540 --> 00:22:28,260
he fell ill of depression

408
00:22:29,140 --> 00:22:29,940
and died.

409
00:22:31,860 --> 00:22:33,140
His wife is left alone.

410
00:22:35,820 --> 00:22:36,780
Seems like

411
00:22:37,100 --> 00:22:38,180
all men in this world

412
00:22:38,500 --> 00:22:39,780
find it most important

413
00:22:39,980 --> 00:22:41,260
to be an official.

414
00:22:57,340 --> 00:22:58,460
Take it easy.

415
00:23:01,180 --> 00:23:01,940
Let me...

416
00:23:06,980 --> 00:23:08,340
Let me explain to you.

417
00:23:19,300 --> 00:23:20,020
Aunt.

418
00:23:20,180 --> 00:23:21,220
Aunt. What’s wrong?

419
00:23:24,180 --> 00:23:24,900
Aunt.

420
00:23:28,740 --> 00:23:29,860
Aunt. What’s wrong?

421
00:23:41,980 --> 00:23:47,140
In this world, there are so many destinies.

422
00:23:49,020 --> 00:23:50,140
We can’t do anything to help.

423
00:23:52,780 --> 00:23:54,820
Your Majesty,

424
00:23:55,700 --> 00:23:57,420
Shunqin would appreciate it

425
00:23:58,340 --> 00:23:59,340
if he knew how much you cared for him.

426
00:24:04,500 --> 00:24:06,940
This is from Mrs. Du?

427
00:24:08,420 --> 00:24:09,420
Is there a letter?

428
00:24:12,900 --> 00:24:14,260
She asked someone to

429
00:24:14,260 --> 00:24:15,540
give the poem to my brother.

430
00:24:17,100 --> 00:24:18,660
His wife sent it to me.

431
00:24:19,580 --> 00:24:22,740
There’s no more letter.

432
00:24:25,500 --> 00:24:28,020
My brother sent Mrs. Du some money.

433
00:24:28,620 --> 00:24:29,970
But she didn’t take it.

434
00:24:31,010 --> 00:24:31,900
She said

435
00:24:33,020 --> 00:24:35,820
she didn’t give me the last poem for mercy,

436
00:24:37,220 --> 00:24:39,020
but she wanted you to read it

437
00:24:40,540 --> 00:24:44,060
and care for those banished officials

438
00:24:44,380 --> 00:24:46,240
like Mr. Fan, Fu Yanguo, Han Zhigui

439
00:24:46,420 --> 00:24:47,700
and Ouyang Yongshu.

440
00:24:50,700 --> 00:24:52,220
When she buries Zimei,

441
00:24:52,820 --> 00:24:55,420
she’ll want nothing else,

442
00:24:56,300 --> 00:24:58,900
if they can write an epigraph for him.

443
00:25:00,700 --> 00:25:02,900
If censors hear you, they’ll complain

444
00:25:03,660 --> 00:25:05,860
for your interfering with politics.

445
00:25:06,820 --> 00:25:07,980
You used to be cautious.

446
00:25:08,340 --> 00:25:10,340
Why are you telling me this today?

447
00:25:25,220 --> 00:25:26,660
Youheng asked for that,

448
00:25:28,220 --> 00:25:30,860
because she was sad of her husband’s death.

449
00:25:32,300 --> 00:25:33,940
She remembered the last words of her husband

450
00:25:34,340 --> 00:25:35,700
and worried about his friends.

451
00:25:37,420 --> 00:25:38,620
She was honest.

452
00:25:39,460 --> 00:25:40,620
I told you whatever she said,

453
00:25:40,620 --> 00:25:41,820
word by word only.

454
00:25:42,540 --> 00:25:43,740
I’ve got no qualms.

455
00:25:46,020 --> 00:25:47,780
Even if censors impeach me,

456
00:25:48,980 --> 00:25:49,860
I won’t regret.

457
00:25:52,860 --> 00:25:54,980
You told me what your close friend said,

458
00:25:55,540 --> 00:25:58,300
concerning banished officials.

459
00:25:58,940 --> 00:26:00,340
Are you interfering with politics?

460
00:26:01,220 --> 00:26:03,940
I’m not sure what censors think.

461
00:26:03,940 --> 00:26:04,660
But...

462
00:26:06,420 --> 00:26:09,780
you’re sad for your friend, who lost her husband.

463
00:26:10,300 --> 00:26:11,420
Whatever you tell me

464
00:26:12,060 --> 00:26:13,740
is between us.

465
00:26:14,420 --> 00:26:15,580
It’s none of others’ business.

466
00:26:26,140 --> 00:26:27,220
In our lives,

467
00:26:28,140 --> 00:26:29,060
it’s great luck

468
00:26:29,060 --> 00:26:30,340
to be husband and wife.

469
00:26:32,260 --> 00:26:33,500
I know

470
00:26:33,500 --> 00:26:35,380
you feel unreconciled and aggrieved.

471
00:26:35,740 --> 00:26:37,220
But you don’t dare to tell me.

472
00:26:39,300 --> 00:26:40,540
If you tell me,

473
00:26:41,940 --> 00:26:43,620
I can help to relax you

474
00:26:43,740 --> 00:26:44,900
and make you happy.

475
00:26:49,260 --> 00:26:50,260
I want you

476
00:26:52,300 --> 00:26:53,660
to tell me directly

477
00:26:53,660 --> 00:26:54,940
no matter you’re happy or sad.

478
00:26:56,060 --> 00:26:56,940
You can chatter.

479
00:26:56,940 --> 00:26:57,820
You can cry.

480
00:26:58,980 --> 00:27:00,580
Or you can even make a scene.

481
00:27:02,380 --> 00:27:03,220
Don’t always solve problems

482
00:27:03,220 --> 00:27:04,860
with your status alone.

483
00:27:05,740 --> 00:27:06,620
When you fail,

484
00:27:06,660 --> 00:27:08,020
you remonstrate with the Emperor

485
00:27:08,260 --> 00:27:10,060
as the Empress.

486
00:27:17,980 --> 00:27:18,700
Come.

487
00:27:29,250 --> 00:27:30,370
That’s the story.

488
00:27:32,570 --> 00:27:33,650
Trust me.

489
00:27:35,490 --> 00:27:37,290
I’m not telling any lie.

490
00:27:40,850 --> 00:27:44,010
Lantiao tried to hurt you.

491
00:27:47,010 --> 00:27:50,650
And she truly killed Yaoyao indirectly.

492
00:27:52,090 --> 00:27:53,170
She deserves to be dead.

493
00:27:55,170 --> 00:27:55,930
But...

494
00:27:57,260 --> 00:27:58,860
she’s pregnant.

495
00:27:59,860 --> 00:28:01,420
And she made the mistake accidentally.

496
00:28:03,420 --> 00:28:05,420
She won’t be executed.

497
00:28:06,380 --> 00:28:09,340
She would be likely to be spared.

498
00:28:10,420 --> 00:28:11,460
I know.

499
00:28:12,500 --> 00:28:14,340
You would rather die with her

500
00:28:14,860 --> 00:28:16,180
than tolerate her.

501
00:28:22,020 --> 00:28:22,860
But she...

502
00:28:24,380 --> 00:28:25,060
She...

503
00:28:25,540 --> 00:28:28,220
She isn’t qualified to die with you.

504
00:28:30,740 --> 00:28:31,900
So, I killed her

505
00:28:33,140 --> 00:28:37,500
for you.

506
00:28:41,260 --> 00:28:42,050
I...

507
00:28:46,620 --> 00:28:47,820
I’m guilty, too.

508
00:28:48,940 --> 00:28:50,540
I’m guilty, too.

509
00:28:52,300 --> 00:28:53,900
The handkerchief...

510
00:28:56,460 --> 00:28:58,860
I used it accidentally.

511
00:29:00,180 --> 00:29:02,820
Later I knew...

512
00:29:03,860 --> 00:29:06,260
I knew Lantiao wanted to serve His Majesty.

513
00:29:08,300 --> 00:29:09,460
But I...

514
00:29:10,340 --> 00:29:11,900
I cared for Xia Song,

515
00:29:12,600 --> 00:29:13,160
And...

516
00:29:14,420 --> 00:29:16,300
And I feared Yang Huaimin.

517
00:29:17,540 --> 00:29:19,380
For the fear that you’re too weak

518
00:29:19,380 --> 00:29:20,460
to defeat Her Highness,

519
00:29:20,860 --> 00:29:22,980
I didn’t tell you anything.

520
00:29:27,590 --> 00:29:28,330
But...

521
00:29:29,670 --> 00:29:30,670
Bihan.

522
00:29:31,860 --> 00:29:32,540
I...

523
00:29:33,820 --> 00:29:34,500
I...

524
00:29:34,860 --> 00:29:38,700
I never try to betray you.

525
00:29:38,940 --> 00:29:40,500
I won’t ever betray you.

526
00:29:42,460 --> 00:29:44,220
Let me say something overwhelming.

527
00:29:48,740 --> 00:29:49,740
All these years,

528
00:29:56,340 --> 00:29:56,980
I...

529
00:29:57,780 --> 00:29:59,020
I always take you

530
00:30:00,700 --> 00:30:02,780
as my...

531
00:30:02,940 --> 00:30:07,060
as my own daughter.

532
00:30:08,820 --> 00:30:09,500
No.

533
00:30:10,540 --> 00:30:11,180
Aunt.

534
00:30:12,100 --> 00:30:13,300
I don’t blame you.

535
00:30:13,780 --> 00:30:15,540
I’m not angry at you, either.

536
00:30:17,020 --> 00:30:18,420
Don’t leave me.

537
00:30:19,220 --> 00:30:21,300
It’s Xu Lantiao’s fault.

538
00:30:22,260 --> 00:30:23,980
You killed her for me.

539
00:30:24,060 --> 00:30:25,220
I don’t blame you.

540
00:30:26,100 --> 00:30:28,380
I’ll beg His Majesty to spare you.

541
00:30:28,980 --> 00:30:30,380
I’m going to see him right away.

542
00:30:30,660 --> 00:30:31,740
I’ll go get a physician.

543
00:30:32,180 --> 00:30:33,260
No. No.

544
00:30:33,260 --> 00:30:33,980
Aunt.

545
00:30:37,860 --> 00:30:39,220
Don’t beg His Majesty.

546
00:30:39,700 --> 00:30:40,860
Don’t beg him.

547
00:30:43,540 --> 00:30:44,500
Zhang Maoze...

548
00:30:45,900 --> 00:30:49,220
He made up his mind

549
00:30:49,660 --> 00:30:50,620
to...

550
00:30:51,260 --> 00:30:53,340
to get you involved

551
00:30:54,620 --> 00:30:55,980
in my mistake.

552
00:30:57,380 --> 00:30:58,220
No.

553
00:31:00,260 --> 00:31:01,340
After I die,

554
00:31:04,060 --> 00:31:05,380
don’t say anything.

555
00:31:06,580 --> 00:31:07,220
You...

556
00:31:08,180 --> 00:31:08,860
Just...

557
00:31:09,220 --> 00:31:10,300
Just let His Majesty...

558
00:31:11,860 --> 00:31:13,500
Let His Majesty see

559
00:31:14,420 --> 00:31:15,820
you’re sad.

560
00:31:17,180 --> 00:31:19,260
Just show him you’re sad.

561
00:31:20,340 --> 00:31:21,060
I’m not scared.

562
00:31:21,660 --> 00:31:23,100
His Majesty will protect me.

563
00:31:23,860 --> 00:31:26,180
Don’t leave me, aunt.

564
00:31:28,700 --> 00:31:31,260
I’ll beg His Majesty to spare you.

565
00:31:33,500 --> 00:31:34,300
Aunt.

566
00:31:36,540 --> 00:31:37,260
Aunt.

567
00:31:38,500 --> 00:31:39,500
Aunt.

568
00:31:40,860 --> 00:31:41,900
Aunt.

569
00:31:45,940 --> 00:31:48,460
Aunt, don’t die.

570
00:32:02,340 --> 00:32:04,900
= Hall of Happiness and Tranquility =

571
00:32:14,420 --> 00:32:15,100
Your Majesty.

572
00:32:16,860 --> 00:32:18,580
I bring Zhang Maoze to you.

573
00:32:20,660 --> 00:32:21,620
Has the physician checked on him?

574
00:32:22,060 --> 00:32:23,060
Is he all right?

575
00:32:24,260 --> 00:32:25,460
Soon after he took poison,

576
00:32:25,580 --> 00:32:27,020
Liaozi found that.

577
00:32:27,420 --> 00:32:28,740
Luckily, he was treated in time.

578
00:32:28,980 --> 00:32:31,100
The poison has been detoxified.

579
00:32:31,220 --> 00:32:32,460
He’s all right, I think.

580
00:32:38,900 --> 00:32:39,780
Let him in.

581
00:32:41,740 --> 00:32:42,460
Aye.

582
00:33:07,500 --> 00:33:08,460
After you nearly died,

583
00:33:08,940 --> 00:33:09,900
how do you feel now?

584
00:33:12,100 --> 00:33:14,740
I’m guilty of your trust and patronage,
Your Majesty.

585
00:33:15,060 --> 00:33:16,140
I’m too ashamed to live.

586
00:33:16,540 --> 00:33:17,900
Please execute me.

587
00:33:19,340 --> 00:33:20,220
Tell me.

588
00:33:21,340 --> 00:33:22,820
Do you admit

589
00:33:23,420 --> 00:33:24,380
what Aunt Jia said in her suicide note?

590
00:33:25,220 --> 00:33:26,740
She is deliberately

591
00:33:27,220 --> 00:33:28,540
framing Her Highness up.

592
00:33:28,780 --> 00:33:29,900
That’s nonsense.

593
00:33:31,100 --> 00:33:32,460
After you die,

594
00:33:33,140 --> 00:33:34,420
will people believe

595
00:33:34,460 --> 00:33:35,780
whatever you’ve done

596
00:33:36,180 --> 00:33:38,020
has nothing to do with the Empress?

597
00:33:40,300 --> 00:33:41,100
Your Majesty.

598
00:33:43,140 --> 00:33:44,540
You know Her Highness.

599
00:33:44,940 --> 00:33:46,220
She’s a noble woman.

600
00:33:47,140 --> 00:33:47,980
How will she

601
00:33:47,980 --> 00:33:49,900
bother about those humble guys?

602
00:33:50,740 --> 00:33:52,420
It’s all my fault.

603
00:33:54,100 --> 00:33:57,420
I hate Madam Zhang

604
00:33:58,180 --> 00:33:59,940
for her vulgarity and arrogance.

605
00:34:01,100 --> 00:34:01,740
I...

606
00:34:01,780 --> 00:34:02,780
So, you set a trap

607
00:34:02,780 --> 00:34:04,460
to frame up Aunt Jia

608
00:34:04,620 --> 00:34:05,660
and Maid Xu?

609
00:34:07,260 --> 00:34:07,900
No.

610
00:34:09,100 --> 00:34:11,740
They had sinister motives.

611
00:34:12,900 --> 00:34:14,420
I hate them.

612
00:34:15,820 --> 00:34:16,460
But I only tracked down

613
00:34:16,460 --> 00:34:17,940
what they have done,

614
00:34:18,980 --> 00:34:20,300
and I didn’t frame them up at all.

615
00:34:24,380 --> 00:34:25,180
But...

616
00:34:28,740 --> 00:34:30,660
But I acted arbitrarily

617
00:34:30,940 --> 00:34:31,940
and I was too bumptious.

618
00:34:32,780 --> 00:34:34,460
I took a wrong step.

619
00:34:36,100 --> 00:34:36,860
I...

620
00:34:38,780 --> 00:34:40,380
I made the prince die

621
00:34:41,780 --> 00:34:42,940
with Maid Xu

622
00:34:44,580 --> 00:34:45,980
before he is born.

623
00:34:46,780 --> 00:34:47,940
I deserve to be executed.

624
00:34:48,820 --> 00:34:50,700
I even deserve to be cut to pieces.

625
00:34:52,220 --> 00:34:54,140
I’ve been serving you for years, Your Majesty.

626
00:34:56,700 --> 00:34:58,060
But I’m still good-for-nothing.

627
00:34:59,300 --> 00:35:01,620
You reminded me many times that

628
00:35:02,460 --> 00:35:03,620
I should be temperate

629
00:35:04,140 --> 00:35:06,700
no matter how I feel,

630
00:35:07,500 --> 00:35:08,620
instead of going to extremes.

631
00:35:10,580 --> 00:35:12,460
Yet I was so dull

632
00:35:15,900 --> 00:35:17,380
that I finally made a big mistake.

633
00:35:19,300 --> 00:35:20,820
I’m too ashamed to live.

634
00:35:30,580 --> 00:35:32,180
Please execute me.

635
00:35:35,580 --> 00:35:36,180
What...

636
00:35:38,500 --> 00:35:39,780
What an idiot you are!

637
00:35:41,500 --> 00:35:42,420
Do you think

638
00:35:42,420 --> 00:35:43,300
I don’t know what you’re planning?

639
00:35:44,060 --> 00:35:44,940
Bumptious!

640
00:35:44,940 --> 00:35:45,780
Smarty-pants!

641
00:35:47,260 --> 00:35:47,650
Since when

642
00:35:47,670 --> 00:35:49,570
were you as selfish as Aunt Jia?

643
00:35:52,060 --> 00:35:54,020
Do you think your death

644
00:35:54,020 --> 00:35:55,540
can vindicate the Empress?

645
00:35:56,420 --> 00:35:58,340
Do you think no one else will think

646
00:35:58,380 --> 00:36:00,180
she ordered you to do that?

647
00:36:02,140 --> 00:36:03,340
If you die,

648
00:36:04,220 --> 00:36:05,380
you’ll bring unredressed injustice

649
00:36:05,380 --> 00:36:06,780
to the Empress.

650
00:36:10,140 --> 00:36:11,260
It’s wise of you, Your Majesty.

651
00:36:13,260 --> 00:36:15,300
Her Highness has never ordered me.

652
00:36:16,380 --> 00:36:17,340
What I did

653
00:36:17,380 --> 00:36:19,180
was the business of Imperial Security Agency.

654
00:36:19,780 --> 00:36:21,860
I’ve never told Her Highness anything.

655
00:36:22,420 --> 00:36:23,340
I was happy

656
00:36:25,700 --> 00:36:27,260
when I found

657
00:36:27,620 --> 00:36:28,980
what Madam Zhang’s maid

658
00:36:29,420 --> 00:36:30,300
had done wrong.

659
00:36:31,580 --> 00:36:33,180
But I never faked any evidence,

660
00:36:35,020 --> 00:36:37,940
tortured or trapped anyone

661
00:36:37,940 --> 00:36:39,540
or anything else against the law

662
00:36:39,820 --> 00:36:40,980
during the investigation.

663
00:36:41,940 --> 00:36:43,100
Then why did you kill yourself?

664
00:36:44,780 --> 00:36:46,100
Aunt Jia killed herself,

665
00:36:47,100 --> 00:36:49,220
because Xia Song is too old

666
00:36:49,580 --> 00:36:51,100
to come back.

667
00:36:53,220 --> 00:36:54,780
After you had the solid evidence,

668
00:36:54,820 --> 00:36:56,060
you would also condemn her.

669
00:36:56,180 --> 00:36:56,940
What about you?

670
00:36:57,780 --> 00:36:58,700
What do others

671
00:36:58,700 --> 00:36:59,820
have on you

672
00:37:00,020 --> 00:37:01,060
so that you had no choice,

673
00:37:01,620 --> 00:37:02,700
but to kill yourself?

674
00:37:04,820 --> 00:37:05,540
I...

675
00:37:09,580 --> 00:37:10,540
You can’t explain,

676
00:37:11,380 --> 00:37:12,780
or you didn’t dare to think about it?

677
00:37:16,900 --> 00:37:18,460
You didn’t disobey any law.

678
00:37:19,780 --> 00:37:21,420
But you were unfair.

679
00:37:22,300 --> 00:37:23,340
You didn’t investigate this case,

680
00:37:23,820 --> 00:37:25,380
because you wanted to uphold justice,

681
00:37:25,860 --> 00:37:27,300
help innocent people

682
00:37:27,820 --> 00:37:28,700
or even for the benefits of

683
00:37:28,700 --> 00:37:29,740
the imperial court or imperial harem.

684
00:37:31,980 --> 00:37:33,620
You were just unfair.

685
00:37:35,100 --> 00:37:36,500
Then you sought the truth

686
00:37:37,180 --> 00:37:38,380
for your own selfish motives.

687
00:37:40,500 --> 00:37:41,500
Seems like

688
00:37:43,460 --> 00:37:45,140
you’re doing everything fair.

689
00:37:45,220 --> 00:37:46,060
But in fact,

690
00:37:46,540 --> 00:37:48,340
you’re as selfish as Aunt Jia.

691
00:37:50,020 --> 00:37:51,220
When you care for someone,

692
00:37:51,820 --> 00:37:52,900
you hate another.

693
00:37:54,020 --> 00:37:55,980
Instead of helping the one you want to help,

694
00:37:56,380 --> 00:37:57,860
you only hurt the one you hate

695
00:37:58,020 --> 00:37:59,380
and get innocent people involved.

696
00:38:01,060 --> 00:38:02,460
Am I right?

697
00:38:08,420 --> 00:38:11,380
I got the innocent prince dead.

698
00:38:13,860 --> 00:38:15,140
I should be executed.

699
00:38:37,100 --> 00:38:38,100
The baby prince...

700
00:38:41,340 --> 00:38:43,300
I named him Zhao Xuan

701
00:38:45,700 --> 00:38:46,740
in my heart.

702
00:38:52,580 --> 00:38:53,340
Your Majesty.

703
00:38:54,620 --> 00:38:55,700
Her Highness sent a maid,

704
00:38:55,860 --> 00:38:57,460
telling about the Double Ninth banquet today.

705
00:38:57,700 --> 00:38:59,580
From one to three p.m.,

706
00:38:59,580 --> 00:39:00,540
royal relatives will come to the backyard,

707
00:39:01,060 --> 00:39:02,380
enjoying the flowers and fishing.

708
00:39:02,620 --> 00:39:04,820
There’re also the ball game and pitch-pot game.

709
00:39:05,820 --> 00:39:07,180
The banquet starts at five.

710
00:39:41,300 --> 00:39:42,140
Stand up.

711
00:39:51,820 --> 00:39:52,700
Your Majesty.

712
00:39:56,700 --> 00:39:57,580
Get up and talk.

713
00:40:33,180 --> 00:40:35,140
I want to tell you some of my true feelings,

714
00:40:37,220 --> 00:40:38,580
like I did in the childhood.

715
00:40:45,020 --> 00:40:45,900
You...

716
00:40:46,900 --> 00:40:47,820
It’s so silly of you.

717
00:40:50,900 --> 00:40:52,700
What’s the relationship between us?

718
00:40:55,100 --> 00:40:57,220
Even if you did the bad things as Aunt Jia,

719
00:40:59,180 --> 00:41:00,900
I would try my best to save you.

720
00:41:02,580 --> 00:41:05,100
Executing people

721
00:41:05,260 --> 00:41:06,780
is the last thing I want to do.

722
00:41:08,660 --> 00:41:09,580
I believe

723
00:41:10,300 --> 00:41:12,100
those who should be executed according to laws

724
00:41:12,940 --> 00:41:15,620
might not deserve it.

725
00:41:18,100 --> 00:41:19,180
I always think

726
00:41:20,220 --> 00:41:21,380
every man has his faults.

727
00:41:24,580 --> 00:41:25,860
Isn’t it better to mend and atone

728
00:41:27,580 --> 00:41:29,740
than to punish them severely?

729
00:41:31,500 --> 00:41:33,140
But it’s not easy to mend.

730
00:41:34,580 --> 00:41:35,500
Things you’ve done,

731
00:41:36,580 --> 00:41:37,700
people you’ve hurt

732
00:41:38,940 --> 00:41:41,380
and the hostility you’ve brought

733
00:41:41,380 --> 00:41:42,620
to the one you care for the most...

734
00:41:44,180 --> 00:41:46,060
You must try your best to make it up,

735
00:41:46,780 --> 00:41:50,300
even if your efforts turn out to be of no avail.

736
00:41:53,980 --> 00:41:54,780
Maoze.

737
00:41:56,700 --> 00:41:58,180
I don’t allow you to die.

738
00:42:03,540 --> 00:42:04,700
I want you to make it up

739
00:42:06,580 --> 00:42:07,620
and atone for your mistakes.

740
00:42:23,700 --> 00:42:25,060
Your Majesty.

741
00:42:33,650 --> 00:42:43,290
♪ Loved you a gentleman yet got abandoned ♪

742
00:42:44,650 --> 00:42:52,970
♪ Peach blossoms color the city ♪

743
00:42:55,810 --> 00:43:00,530
♪ Spring breeze purified dusty memories ♪

744
00:43:01,530 --> 00:43:05,690
♪ The gate of the vast palace opens ♪

745
00:43:07,130 --> 00:43:12,610
♪ Bid farewell with wine after the glory ends ♪

746
00:43:12,610 --> 00:43:17,370
♪ Outside the city a beautiful world unveils ♪

747
00:43:21,050 --> 00:43:26,690
♪ Long-standing distance doesn’t alienate us ♪

748
00:43:26,690 --> 00:43:31,610
♪ Keep you company behind the gate ♪

749
00:43:32,090 --> 00:43:37,850
♪ Four seasons come and go ♪

750
00:43:37,850 --> 00:43:42,930
♪ We only have each other in this cage ♪

751
00:43:43,370 --> 00:43:48,290
♪ Wish to fly freely in the next life ♪

752
00:43:48,930 --> 00:43:53,770
♪ Willows turn green flowers red ♪

753
00:43:54,450 --> 00:43:59,610
♪ Sing aloud with wine ♪

754
00:44:00,130 --> 00:44:05,170
♪ Hold your hands and go home together ♪

755
00:44:05,690 --> 00:44:09,770
♪ Be a pair of swallows in the next life ♪

756
00:44:11,250 --> 00:44:15,890
♪ Build the nest and protect the nestlings ♪

757
00:44:16,890 --> 00:44:22,050
♪ The howling wind ♪

758
00:44:22,410 --> 00:44:26,490
♪ Woke me up from the dream ♪

759
00:44:27,970 --> 00:44:32,890
♪ Be a pair of swallows in the next life ♪

760
00:44:33,570 --> 00:44:38,770
♪ Build the nest and protect the nestlings ♪

761
00:44:39,210 --> 00:44:44,490
♪ The howling wind ♪

762
00:44:44,770 --> 00:44:49,650
♪ Woke me up from the dream ♪

763
00:44:50,250 --> 00:44:56,970
♪ Life is long yet joy is little ♪
